net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component

Class ComboBox

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComboBox
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Component>, EventListener, LocaleContextSource, CardContainerSelector, Component, Editable, ListModelComponent, TableCellEditor, TableCellRenderer, TreeCellEditor, TreeCellRenderer, ListDataListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SearchableComboBox

    public class ComboBox
extends ComponentImpl
implements Editable, ListDataListener, ListModelComponent, TableCellRenderer, TableCellEditor, TreeCellRenderer, TreeCellEditor, CardContainerSelector

    A ComboBox component allows the user to select exactly one choice from a list. The UI is normally a drop down list. If the component is editable the user may also enter text for their choice.

    Selection changes are sent through the selection model's ListSelectionListener events. ActionListener events are sent whenever the control is used, even if the selection does not not change.

    This component may be used as a table cell renderer/editor. The appropriate cell renderer/editor method must be called to behave correctly as a table cell renderer/editor. The selection model will NOT be updated when used in this manner, the model will be updated directly.

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • init

        public void init()
        Description copied from interface: Component

        Called when a Component is first attached to a WindowManager. This means the Component should have valid return values from getApplication(), getLocaleContext(), getParent(). It is preferable to have all construction of the Component go here since a valid LocaleContext, Application object, etc., are available.

        When overriding this method, be sure to call the super class init(). init() is called only once for each Component. The parent component will have been init()ed before init() is called.

        NOTE: Do not call this method from application code. It is meant to be called by the WindowManager only.

        Specified by:
        init in interface Component
        Overrides:
        init in class ComponentImpl
